================================================================================
 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
================================================================================

 The optimizations reduced total instruction count by 2.33 BILLION instructions,
 a 7.82% reduction in total program cost.

 All savings came from replacing expensive glibc math library calls with
 fast inline approximations or simple multiplications.

 No ray tracing core logic was changed. hit_object, hit_sphere, add_lighting,
 and all other rendering functions have IDENTICAL instruction counts.

 Key results at a glance:

   ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────────┬─────────────┐
   │ Metric                          │ BEFORE       │ AFTER       │
   ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┼─────────────┤
   │ Total instructions (Ir)         │ 29,803 M     │ 27,472 M    │
   │ Total branches (Bc)             │ 1,275 M      │    978 M    │
   │ Branch mispredictions (Bcm)     │    32.1 M    │   23.9 M    │
   │ Indirect branches (Bi)          │    77.1 M    │   38.4 M    │
   │ Indirect branch misses (Bim)    │   873 K      │  873 K      │
   └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────────┴─────────────┘

   Instructions saved:  2,331,442,026  (−7.82%)
   Branches saved:        296,719,911  (−23.27%)
   Br. mispred. saved:      8,194,174  (−25.51%)
   Indirect br. saved:     38,622,480  (−50.12%)


