 4. OPTIMIZATION A: atan2f → fast_atan2f
================================================================================

 WHAT CHANGED:
   spherical_uv() in mapping.c used to call glibc's atan2f().
   Now it calls fast_atan2f() from fast_math.c.

 BEFORE — glibc atan2f call chain:
 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   atan2f wrapper (w_atan2f_compat.c):
     Line 32:  49,909,060 Ir
     Line 35:  69,872,684 Ir  (+ 9,981,812 branches, 7 mispred)
     Line 38:  39,927,248 Ir
     Line 39:  69,872,692 Ir  (+ 9,981,813 branches, 426,494 mispred)
     Line 42:  19,963,624 Ir
     ─────────────────────────
     Subtotal: 249,545,308 Ir

   atanf internal (s_atanf.c):
     Lines 58-101 total:       575,619,084 Ir
     (includes polynomial evaluation, range reduction, branch checks)
     Branch misses:  ~3,113,330 (very hard for CPU to predict!)

   TOTAL atan2f BEFORE: ~825,164,392 Ir
                        ~48,968,262 branches
                        ~3,539,831 mispredictions

 AFTER — fast_atan2f (fast_math.c):
 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   fast_atan2f (fast_math.c):
     Line 0:   29,945,433 Ir  (function entry overhead)
     Line 16:  29,945,433 Ir
     Line 17:   9,981,811 Ir
     Line 18:  29,945,433 Ir
     Line 19:   9,981,811 Ir
     Line 20:  39,927,244 Ir
     Line 21:  29,945,433 Ir
     Line 23:  39,927,244 Ir
     Line 25:  39,927,244 Ir
     Line 27:   9,981,811 Ir
     ─────────────────────────
     Subtotal: 269,508,897 Ir
     Branches: 0   (branchless polynomial!)
     Mispredictions: 0

   atan2f wrapper residual (only called 1x for init, not per-pixel):
     Lines 32-42 total:  33 Ir  (negligible)

   TOTAL atan2f AFTER:  ~269,508,930 Ir

 SAVINGS:
   Ir:  −555,655,462  (−67.3%)
   Bc:  −48,968,262   (branches eliminated entirely!)
   Bcm: −3,539,831    (mispredictions eliminated entirely!)

 WHY IT'S SAFE:
   Max error ~0.3° — invisible under Monte Carlo noise (~1-5%).
   The fast polynomial is completely branchless, which also helps
   CPU pipeline efficiency beyond what instruction count shows.


