 6. OPTIMIZATION C: powf → fast_srgb (GAMMA CORRECTION)
================================================================================

 WHAT CHANGED:
   linear_to_srgb() in post_processing.c used to call powf(x, 1/2.2).
   Now it calls fast_srgb(x) from fast_math.c.

 BEFORE — glibc powf call chain:
 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   __powf_fma (e_powf.c):
     Lines 55-231 total:       855,832,144 Ir
     (includes logf, expf internally — the full exp(y*log(x)) path)
     Branch misses:  ~74,782

   __powf_fma (math_config.h — lookup tables):
     Line 67:  37,325,312 Ir
     Line 89:  12,361,904 Ir
     ─────────────────────────
     Subtotal: 49,687,216 Ir

   TOTAL powf→gamma BEFORE: ~905,519,360 Ir

   Note: powf was called 3× per pixel (once per R,G,B channel) ×
   6,220,800 pixels = 18,662,400 calls total. That's why ~12.36M
   appears as the base count in many lines (12,361,904 ≈ 2× per pixel
   after inlining, × 6,220,800).

   post_process function itself BEFORE: ~68,428,800 Ir at line 0
   (function entry overhead includes the powf callsite cost)

 AFTER — fast_srgb (fast_math.c):
 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   fast_srgb (fast_math.c):
     Line 0:   12,361,638 Ir
     Line 58:  37,324,800 Ir
     Line 62:  37,324,800 Ir  (+ 18,662,400 branches, 69,529 mispred)
     Line 64:  12,361,638 Ir
     Line 65:  12,361,638 Ir
     Line 66:  24,723,276 Ir
     Line 67:  18,662,400 Ir
     ─────────────────────────
     Subtotal: 155,120,190 Ir

   __powf_fma residual (only called ~255 times for init, not per-pixel):
     Lines 55-231 total:  ~11,835 Ir  (negligible)

   post_process function itself AFTER: ~62,208,000 Ir at line 0.
   The 6,220,800 Ir reduction at the function entry corresponds to the
   eliminated overhead from calling powf (function call setup).

   TOTAL powf→gamma AFTER: ~155,120,190 Ir

 SAVINGS:
   Ir:  ~750,399,170  (−82.9%)

   This is the SINGLE BIGGEST optimization by absolute Ir saved.

 powf before vs fast_srgb after, per call:
   powf per call:      ~905,519,360 / 18,662,400 ≈ 49 Ir/call
   fast_srgb per call: ~155,120,190 / 18,662,400 ≈  8 Ir/call
   Speedup: ~6.1x fewer instructions per call

 WHY IT'S SAFE:
   - Output is 8-bit sRGB (only 256 levels per channel)
   - Blue noise dithering adds ±0.5/255 per channel anyway
   - Max error ~1.7% in midtones, <1% in highlights/shadows
   - The dithering noise is larger than the approximation error


================================================================================
 7. OPTIMIZATION D: powf(1-u, 5) → MULTIPLY (SCHLICK FRESNEL)
================================================================================

 WHAT CHANGED:
   f_schlick() and vec3_schlick() used to call powf(1-u, 5.0f).
   Now they compute t=1-u; t2=t*t; result=t2*t2*t (4 multiplications).

 ANALYSIS:
   The Schlick functions (f_schlick, vec3_schlick) show IDENTICAL Ir
   counts in before and after:

   f_schlick:
     BEFORE: 0→11,243,224 Ir | 22→78,702,568 Ir
     AFTER:  0→11,243,224 Ir | 22→78,702,568 Ir
     DIFF:   0 (identical)

   vec3_schlick:
     BEFORE: 0→58,596,976 | 29→29,298,488 | 32→58,596,976 | 33→131,843,196
     AFTER:  0→58,596,976 | 29→29,298,488 | 32→58,596,976 | 33→131,843,196
     DIFF:   0 (identical)

 IMPORTANT NOTE:
   The Schlick optimization's savings are INVISIBLE in these two functions
   because the powf calls were made FROM f_schlick/vec3_schlick INTO the
   external __powf_fma function. The savings appear in the __powf_fma
   totals (Section 6 above).

   The massive drop in __powf_fma (from 905M Ir → ~12K Ir) reflects
   BOTH optimization C (gamma powf eliminated) AND optimization D
   (Schlick powf eliminated).

   Estimated Schlick contribution to powf savings:
     Schlick is called ~7.3M times per render (f_schlick + vec3_schlick).
     Each powf call cost ~49 Ir. Total: ~358M Ir from Schlick's powf.
     After: 4 multiplications ≈ 4 Ir. Total: ~29M Ir.
     Estimated savings from D alone: ~329M Ir (~2.4% of program total)

 WHY IT'S SAFE:
   - ZERO approximation error (mathematically identical:
     (1-u)^5 = ((1-u)²)² × (1-u) — exact same floating-point result)
   - The change is just telling the compiler to use multiplications
     instead of having glibc compute exp(5 * log(1-u))


